Server : machine and software that provide information to clients
Data are provided over HTTP
Client : anything that can make HTPP requests

Nginx and server logs
First we need create a server that will accept HTTP request, we are going the user the Nginx server image from docker
$docker image pull nginx
To run automatically remove the container after use add --rm and redirect all the coming http traffic from port 80 to port 80 on our nginx web server
$docker container run --rm -p 80:80 nginx
Warning : not running in a daemonized mode

On the kali side we are making a request using curl
$curl http://servertcm or IP address
or 
$nc servertcm 80
or use web browser

HTTP
Protocol that defines how web traffic is structured 
Methods:
GET : ask the server to give information
POST : send data to the server (adding a comment, logging into your account)
PUT and PATCH : represent updates to exising data
DELETE : delete a resource
HEAD and OPTIONS : metadata request to the server (its capacities)

Every request response has a response code
200:success
300 : redirect
400 : failed access
500 : error
Responses can have a body (json, binary data)

Use -v when using curl to get more info such as IP address and connection data such as encryption details for https
Add -L to curl to follow redirection. If you curl an hhtp site with a https redirection the -L follows that redirection
$curl -L -v http://site
$curl -v https://site

If we want to send a POST request
$curl -X POST -v https://site
Can use a custom header
$curl -X POST https://site -H "User-Agent : PWST" //change user-agent

Zaproxy
Setting up:
-On brave create new profile
-Add Proxy SwitchyOmega from google web store
-Add Wappalyzer the same way

Then we configure switchyproxy:
-First we go in the profile section to change the "proxy" profile name to "ZAP"
-In the ZAP profile we enter "localhost" in the server box and keep the port 8080
-Do not forget to click on "Apply Changes"

Next step is to launch zaproxy
An add-ons windows opens, we need to update all by clicking at the bottom of the page. May need to resize the window
Switch on the web browser to ZAP profile on Switchy Proxy
We need to set the zap certificate in the browser
-Click on option gear
-Scroll to dynamic ssl certificate or Network > Server Certificates
-Save it and dowload it in the browser in the security section > Authorities

By starting an automatic attack, using the spider (enables the enumeration of the links of the site), we can add a context to the site using rigth click > Include in Context > New Context > OK. Once done we can select the outputs and study the requests and responses.

We can now download a few add-ons on the marketplace (red,blue and green cubes)
Then we click on the option gear > Global Exclude URL to add brave in exclude url following the syntax given for other sites:
^https?://.*\.brave\.com.*$

